description: From Latin praesignificare, from prae (“before”) + significare (“to signify”).

verbs.description: presignify (third-person singular simple present presignifies, present participle presignifying, simple past and past participle presignified)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To intimate or signify beforehand; to presage.
examples: That owls and ravens are ominous appearers, and presignifying unlucky events, as Christians yet conceit, was also an augurial conception.
